==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gladly
<hw>Glad"ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Glad</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Preferably; by choice.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>With pleasure; joyfully; cheerfully;
eagerly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The common people heard him <qex>gladly</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Mark
xii. 37.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gladness</ent>⟦br⟧
